cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "RePERS — Reusable Planning, Execution, Review, and Release harness for agent-run repository work"
message: "If you reference this harness in academic work or technical writing, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "coolsocket"
    website: "https://github.com/coolsocket"
repository-code: "https://github.com/coolsocket/repers"
url: "https://github.com/coolsocket/repers"
abstract: >-
  A local-first harness that turns a vague engineering request into a
  repeatable agent workflow: preflight (capability discovery) → task DAG →
  conflict-safe worker lanes → join/review → installable package → transferable
  release pack with JSON evidence. Ships a 24-entry capability registry, a
  deterministic orchestration fixture, a Codex plugin with 4 skills
  (init / bug-hunt / release-pack / sinkin), a Git pre-commit hook, and
  round-trippable release archives. Designed for agents and maintainers who
  need more than a chat transcript — every step produces machine-readable
  evidence another repo can verify.
keywords:
